 Dunamis International Gospel Centre has removed Sammie Okposo‘s name from the lineup of gospel artists scheduled to minister at their concert on Friday as a result of his confession on Tuesday about cheating on his wife. The Wellu Wellu master, as he is fondly called, turned to Instagram to explain that he was in an intimate relationship with another woman when he traveled to the United States. READ ALSO: Leave The Ministry, Media Personality, Bolanle Olukanle Reacts To Sammie Okposo’s Extramarital Affair Nigerians have reacted to the news in a variety of ways on social media. According to a brochure posted earlier today on the senior pastor Dr Paul Enenche’s Instagram page, Okposo’s name and photo have been removed from the minister’s list. Artists such as Sinach, Nathaniel Bassey, and others will continue to perform at the event. See post below:   A post shared by Dr Paul Enenche (@drpastorpaulenenche) 